From 02bfa282bfab272eb06b403f333a16c919cf13ea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 13:47:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix: Orbit must not reuse GDTF mesh after custom replace
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Orbit dedupes Objects.Geometry.Mesh by applicationId. Stable ids like
`${fixture}:${part}:0` caused republish after Settings → Replace to keep the
prior GDTF head/base geometry. Stamp mediaId into applicationId, keep client
meshOffset when preserving stored replacement media, translate-only offsets for
custom meshes, clear stale offsets on slot-dim heal, carry custom meshes across
reimport, and sync PUT definitions to the active version.
